Another 19 Aug 2016 report indicated that CDC experts estimate that there have been 270 babies born with microcephaly to mothers infected with Zika virus during pregnancy in Puerto Rico. (http://www.swissinfo.ch/spa/reuters/puerto-rico-registrar%C3%ADa-hasta-270-casos-de-microcefalia-por-virus-de-zika--funcionarios/42385834 [in Spanish)]).

